  { question: "What are typical closing costs when flipping a house?", answer: "Buyer closing costs are typically 1-3% of the purchase price and include title insurance, inspections, and loan fees. Seller closing costs are higher at 5-8% of the sale price, primarily due to real estate agent commissions (typically 5-6%) plus transfer taxes and title fees." },
